    {
      "id": "ZUsWg9ed6WvneIz6WSsIJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 156.10002056671968,
      "y": 8322.265138786412,
      "width": 971.979248046875,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0V",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1854934886,
      "version": 733,
      "versionNonce": 1483609446,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770027713374,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Decision of rate limiting algorithm: \n1. going forward with token bucket is a better way of handling things, helps with the sudden burst.\n2. token bucket, leaking bucket, sliding window, rolling sliding window.\n\nDeep Dives: \n1. How to scale to 1M req/sec\n   \n    what will get hammered?\n    50k to 100k req/sec\n\n2. How to ensure high availability and high fault tolerence\n    \nin case of network partition keep serving from what you have, so here \nfor availability, fail open strategy would have to be implemented so that\nwe keep serving even if the rate limiter goes down.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Decision of rate limiting algorithm: \n1. going forward with token bucket is a better way of handling things, helps with the sudden burst.\n2. token bucket, leaking bucket, sliding window, rolling sliding window.\n\nDeep Dives: \n1. How to scale to 1M req/sec\n   \n    what will get hammered?\n    50k to 100k req/sec\n\n2. How to ensure high availability and high fault tolerence\n    \nin case of network partition keep serving from what you have, so here \nfor availability, fail open strategy would have to be implemented so that\nwe keep serving even if the rate limiter goes down.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "FVmMAyM6sKi4MVBzjzNbG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -106.65111623259327,
      "y": 8892.984077107658,
      "width": 1065.17919921875,
      "height": 1125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0W",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 750349478,
      "version": 1569,
      "versionNonce": 679059282,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770141158818,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3rd Feb 2026\n\nJob Scheduler\n\nFR:\n1. user should be able to schedule\njobs to be executed immedieately, \nat a future date or on a recurring\nschedule.\n2. user should be able to monitor the\nstatus of the job.\n\n\nNFR:\n1. availability > consistency\n2. scale - scalable upto 10k jobs per second\n3. latency - execute jobs within 2 secs of their scheduled time\n4. durability - should ensure atleast once execution.\n                        \n                            BTL\n\n1. should ensure security policies\n2. should provide CI/CD pipelines.\n\n\nCore Entities\n1. jobs\n2. schedule\n3. user\n4. tasks\n\nAPI\n1. POST /jobs\n{\n    task_id,\n    schedule,\n    parameters: {}\n} \n2. GET /jobs?user_id={user_id}&status={status}&start_time={start_time}&end_time={end_time} -> Job[]\n\nData Flow\n1. user creates tasks\n2. user schedules jobs\n3. the scheduler runs jobs\n4. updates the status of the job",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3rd Feb 2026\n\nJob Scheduler\n\nFR:\n1. user should be able to schedule\njobs to be executed immedieately, \nat a future date or on a recurring\nschedule.\n2. user should be able to monitor the\nstatus of the job.\n\n\nNFR:\n1. availability > consistency\n2. scale - scalable upto 10k jobs per second\n3. latency - execute jobs within 2 secs of their scheduled time\n4. durability - should ensure atleast once execution.\n                        \n                            BTL\n\n1. should ensure security policies\n2. should provide CI/CD pipelines.\n\n\nCore Entities\n1. jobs\n2. schedule\n3. user\n4. tasks\n\nAPI\n1. POST /jobs\n{\n    task_id,\n    schedule,\n    parameters: {}\n} \n2. GET /jobs?user_id={user_id}&status={status}&start_time={start_time}&end_time={end_time} -> Job[]\n\nData Flow\n1. user creates tasks\n2. user schedules jobs\n3. the scheduler runs jobs\n4. updates the status of the job",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "d6tM2T1lENnKZEbAT3I4z",
